IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SKILLED NURSING SERVICES AND ASSISTED LIVING SERVICES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: QUALITY CARE AND SERVICES THAT SHAPE THE FUTURE FOR THE DYNAMIC NEEDS OF THE PEOPLE IN OUR AREA.
IRS990.Desc: THE ORGANIZATION OPERATES A 45 BED SKILLED NURSING FACILITY, A 56 UNIT ASSISTED LIVING BUILDING (A.K.A CENTENNIAL VILLA ASSISTED LIVING), A 42 UNIT ASSISTED LIVING BUILDING (A.K.A PLEASANT VISTA ASSISTED LIVING), A 29 UNIT MEMORY CARE FACILITY AND A WELLNESS CENTER. IT NOT ONLY PROVIDES SERVICES TO THE ELDERLY POPULATION IN ANNANDALE BUT ALSO TO THOSE IN OTHER AREA COMMUNITIES WHICH HELPS THE INDIVIDUAL TO REMAIN IN THE SAME GEOGRAPHICAL AREA OF THEIR FORMER RESIDENCE. THE SKILLED NURSING FACILITY HAS AN EXCELLENT THERAPY PROGRAM THAT IS AVAILABLE TO ITS RESIDENTS WHO ARE IN NEED OF REHABILITATION SERVICES. IT ALSO HAS AN OUTPATIENT PROGRAM THAT TREATS THOSE FROM THE ANNANDALE COMMUNITY AND THE SURROUNDING AREA. IT IS BECAUSE OF ITS ONSITE THERAPY PROGRAM THAT IT HAS BECOME THE FIRST CHOICE FOR MOST WHEN THEY REQUIRE REHABILITATION SERVICES FOLLOWING A SURGERY IN ORDER TO RETURN HOME SAFELY. THE ASSISTED LIVING BUILDING SERVES AS A PLEASANT TRANSITION FOR THOSE WHO NEED ADDITIONAL HELP THAT IS NOT READILY AVAILABLE IN THEIR OWN HOME BUT ARE STILL INDEPENDENT ENOUGH THAT THEY DON'T REQUIRE THE SERVICES OF A SKILLED NURSING FACILITY. THE MEMORY LOSS UNIT IS MUCH MORE APPROPRIATE FOR THOSE WHO SUFFER FROM ALZHEIMER'S AND/OR SEVERE DEMENTIA THAN A SKILLED NURSING FACILITY. THE ENVIRONMENT IS CONTROLLED AND SETUP TO MEET EACH RESIDENT'S NEEDS RELATING TO THEIR SPECIFIC ILLNESS. THE WELLNESS CENTER HAS A THERAPY/EXERCISE SWIM POOL, EXERCISE CLASS STUDIO AND AN EXERCISE EQUIPMENT ROOM DEVELOPED TO SERVE THE WELLNESS NEEDS OF THOSE 50 YEARS OF AGE AND OLDER - BOTH WITHIN THE CAMPUS AND THE OUTSIDE COMMUNITY. THE WELLNESS CENTER WAS CLOSED FROM SPRING 2020 THROUGH FEBRURARY 2022. IT WAS RE-OPENED IN MARCH 2022.ANNANDALE CONGREGATE HOUSING MERGED INTO THE ORGANIZATION AS OF JULY 31ST, 2021. WITH THE MERGER, THE ORGANIZATION NOW ALSO OPERATES A 22 UNIT CONGREGATE HOUSING FACILITY THAT SERVES THE HOUSING NEEDS OF THE 55 AND OLDER ADULT POPULATION IN ANNANDALE AND THE SURROUNDING COMMUNITIES. RESIDENTS HAVE ACCESS TO PREPARED MEALS AND 24 HOUR EMERGENCY RESPONSE FROM THE NURSING STAFF IN THE ATTACHED SKILLED NURSING FACILITY. THEY ALSO HAVE PRIORITY IN THE EVENT THAT THEY REQUIRE A NURSING HOME STAY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNANDALE CARE CENTER ACTS AS CUSTODIAN FOR FUNDS OF ITS RESIDENTS AND TENANTS.

THE CARE CENTER IS ORGANIZED AS MINNESOTA NONPROFIT CORPORATION AND HAS BEEN RECOGNIZED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) AS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3). THE CARE CENTER IS ANNUALLY REQUIRED TO FILE A RETURN OF ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX (FORM 990) WITH THE IRS. IN ADDITION, THE CARE CENTER IS SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX ON NET INCOME THAT IS DERIVED FROM BUSINESS ACTIVITIES THAT ARE UNRELATED TO THEIR EXEMPT PURPOSES. THE CARE CENTER HAS DETERMINED THEY ARE NOT SUBJECT TO UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME TAX AND HAVE NOT FILED AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION BUSINESS INCOME TAX RETURN (FORM 990T) WITH THE IRS. THE CARE CENTER BELIEVES THAT THEY HAVE APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN AFFECTING THEIR ANNUAL FILING REQUIREMENTS, AND AS SUCH, DO NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE CARE CENTER WILL RECOGNIZE FUTURE ACCRUED INTEREST AND PENALTIES RELATED TO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS AND LIABILITIES IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE IF SUCH INTEREST AND PENALTIES ARE INCURRED.

SCHOLARSHIPS ARE AWARDED TO EMPLOYEES WHO WORK AN AVERAGE OF 20 HOURS A WEEK OR MORE AND WHO ARE ENROLLED IN A PROGRAM OF STUDY RELATED TO LONG TERM CARE. RECIPIENTS ARE SELECTED BY A COMMITTEE ON A QUARTERLY BASIS. FUNDS ARE DISBURSED UPON RECEIVING A COPY OF THE RECIPIENT'S TUITION/FEES STATEMENT AND/OR RECEIPTS FOR PURCHASES OF REQUIRED TEXTBOOKS. THE GUIDELINES FOR THIS PROGRAM ARE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THOSE SET FORTH BY THE MN DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN SERVICES' NURSING FACILITY SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESIDENT DOES NOT HAVE VOTING RIGHTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS ELECTED ANNUALLY BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF ANNANDALE HEALTH AND COMMUNITY SERVICES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FOLLOWING MUST BE APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF ANNANDALE HEALTH AND COMMUNITY SERVICES: - BUDGET - CHANGES IN BUDGET OF OVER $10,000 - EXPENDITURES OF OVER $10,000 - SALES OF ASSETS OF OVER $10,000 - CHANGES TO THE BYLAWS THE FOLLOWING MUST BE APPROVED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE ANNANDALE HEALTH AND COMMUNITY SERVICE BOARD: - CHANGES IN THE BUDGET OF OVER $5,000 BUT LESS THAN $10,000 - EXPENDITURES OF OVER $5,000 BUT LESS THAN $10,000 - SALES OF ASSETS OF OVER $5,000 BUT LESS THAN $10,000

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE ARE NO COMMITTEES THAT CAN ACT ON BEHALF OF THE BOARD. COMMITTEES MUST COME BACK TO THE FULL BOARD TO MAKE A FINAL DECISION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 WILL BE REVIEWED BY THE ADMINISTRATOR, CONTROLLER AND THE BOARD PRIOR TO FINALIZING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE IS NO ANNUAL FORM OR DISCLOSURE THAT IS USED TO UNCOVER CONFLICTS OF INTEREST; HOWEVER, INDIVIDUALS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST BASED ON AN "HONOR-SYSTEM." ANYONE WHO CAN INFLUENCE THE ACTIONS OF THE CORPORATION IS COVERED BY THE POLICY. THIS INCLUDES BOARD MEMBERS, KEY EMPLOYEES, OFFICERS, AND EMPLOYEES. THE BOARD REVIEWS AND DETERMINES WHEN AND IF A CONFLICT EXISTS. IF A CONFLICT EXISTS, BOARD MEMBERS ARE NOT ALLOWED TO VOTE ON THE ISSUE IN CONFLICT. ALL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ARE DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MEETING MINUTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL SALARIES ARE COMPARED TO THE INDUSTRY AVERAGES AND WEIGHTED WITH EXPERIENCE AND EDUCATION PRIOR TO A DECISION BEING MADE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES IT GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST. THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE NOT MADE PUBLICLY AVAILABLE.
